news.title: Allahabad HC refuses to quash ED proceedings in Grand Venice case
news.para: The Allahabad High Court refused to quash ED proceedings under PMLA for the Grand Venice project, but raised questions about jurisdiction if only Section 406 IPC remains. The court directed the ED to halt coercive measures until charges are framed or a final order is passed on consolidated FIRs.

news.title: Telangana housing board announces sale of LIG flats in Hyderabad
news.para: The Telangana Housing Board is selling 339 one-bedroom flats for the Lower Income Group in Gachibowli, Warangal, and Khammam. Priced below market rates, these homes are for individuals earning up to Rs 6 lakh annually. Lotteries for Gachibowli, Warangal, and Khammam flats are scheduled for January 6, 8, and 10 respectively.

news.title: Haryana govt extends settlement scheme to expedite EDC recovery from developers
news.para: Haryana has extended its 'Samadhan Se Vikas' scheme until March 31, 2026, for pending external development charges. New terms include a 1% monthly interest hike after September 15, 2025, for full settlements and increased upfront payments for partial settlements to encourage timely developer payments and fund crucial infrastructure.

news.title: Elon Musk's Starlink leases first office space with CorporatEdge in New Delhi
news.para: Elon Musk-owned Starlink has secured its first office space in northern India, leasing a 50-seater facility at Delhi's World Trade Center. This move, alongside OpenAI's similar decision, signals a strategic choice for proximity to the capital's power centers and a preference for flexible, premium workspace providers.

news.title: Lucknow civic body to track tax of every residential and commercial property
news.para: Lucknow Municipal Corporation is launching a new Property Tax Management System (PTMS) to digitally track property tax assessment, collection, and dues. This system will assign unique 16-digit IDs to all properties, linked to GIS mapping and a Smart City Command and Control Centre for enhanced transparency and compliance.

news.title: Redevelopment wave reshapes Gujarat’s real estate landscape
news.para: Gujarat's real estate sector is experiencing a significant shift towards redevelopment and joint development projects, driven by soaring land prices.  This partnership model offers landowners better returns than outright sales, while developers benefit from reduced upfront land acquisition costs.  The trend is particularly strong in Ahmedabad, with a notable increase in registered development agreements.

news.title: Backlog of 3,228 illegal construction cases overwhelms Goa's panchayat courts
news.para: Over 3,200 illegal construction cases are overwhelming Goa's panchayat judicial system, with experts citing a deliberate weakening of local governance. A flawed workflow, initiated by changes in 2010, allows the Town and Country Planning department to bypass panchayats, leading to appeals and indefinite delays that benefit the construction lobby.

news.title: Homebuyers seek stronger Karnataka RERA enforcement for ownership rights
news.para: Citing delays by builders, the Karnataka Home Buyers’ Forum wants automatic title transfer after five years, mandatory association registration, model bylaws, fair elections, and appellate mechanisms to protect flat owners.

news.title: Delhi HC penalises 'serial litigant' for filing multiple pleas against illegal constructions
news.para: In a stern reminder of judicial etiquette, the Delhi High Court imposed a penalty of Rs 50,000 on a petitioner whose relentless efforts regarding illegal constructions had turned into a futile exercise. Despite multiple petitions, the court observed a pattern of non-compliance from the petitioner.

news.title: Japan's Sumitomo Realty puts India bet on Mumbai and serviced apartments
news.para: Japanese developer Sumitomo Realty and Development is taking a refreshing approach to real estate in India by opting for a rental management strategy instead of the traditional sales route, particularly in  Mumbai.

news.title: Cement manufacturers’ association appoints Parth Jindal as president
news.para: Parth Jindal has been elected president of the Cement Manufacturers’ Association, becoming the youngest to hold the post. He succeeds Neeraj Akhoury and will focus on sustainability, decarbonisation, logistics efficiency and policy engagement to strengthen the cement industry’s global competitiveness.

news.title: Acquire land for airport in four months: HC to Meghalaya
news.para: In a significant ruling, the Meghalaya High Court has mandated the Ri-Bhoi deputy commissioner and the transport department to hasten the acquisition of 11.75 acres required for the expansion of Shillong Airport, with a deadline set for January 10.

news.title: Gurugram-Noida RRTS route takes shape, six stations in draft detailed project report
news.para: A new rapid rail corridor is proposed between Gurgaon's IFFCO Chowk and Greater Noida's Surajpur, costing an estimated Rs 15,000 crore. This crucial link aims to connect IGI Airport with the upcoming Jewar Airport. Haryana government has suggested an underground route within Gurgaon, citing land costs and urban density, while NCRTC prefers an elevated line.

news.title: CAG report flags lapses in housing scheme in Chhattisgarh
news.para: The recent CAG report unveils significant shortcomings in Chhattisgarh's welfare and infrastructure initiatives. Concerns were raised regarding the selection process of beneficiaries and mishandling of funds related to urban housing projects. Moreover, labor welfare schemes displayed a troubling trend of fund underutilization and insufficient worker registrations.

news.title: Vadodara civic body gets ₹235 crore grant for urban projects
news.para: Vadodara Municipal Corporation (VMC) received a Rs 235 crore grant under the Swarnim Jayanti Mukhyamantri Shaheri Vikas Yojana, bringing the total released to Rs 365 crore. The funds, part of a larger Rs 455 crore allocation, will be used for various urban development projects. The cheque was presented by Chief Minister Bhupendra Patel.

news.title: Bengaluru: BDA, forest department to hold joint survey to resolve Banashankari land dispute
news.para: A joint survey by BDA and the forest department is scheduled in two weeks to resolve a land dispute affecting hundreds of site owners in Banashankari 6th Stage. This follows conflicting claims over 16 acres, potentially impacting a 100-meter buffer zone around BM Kaval Agara forest land.

news.title: Compound wall collapse prompts evacuation from 192 apartments in Surat
news.para: Residents of 192 apartments at Shiv Residency were evacuated after a deep foundation pit's retaining wall collapsed, causing the compound wall to cave in. The Surat Municipal Corporation suspended licenses of four individuals for negligence, citing water accumulation and soil settlement as probable causes for the incident.

news.title: About 50,000 paperless property registrations done in Haryana: Financial commissioner
news.para: Haryana has successfully completed nearly 50,000 property registrations using its new paperless system, a significant shift in revenue practices. The state plans to introduce security-embedded paper and an auto-mutation facility to enhance transparency and efficiency. E-signed copies will be provided on the spot to applicants upon request.

news.title: Hubballi smart city houses remain vacant as families wait for keys
news.para: Smart City homes for families displaced by road expansion in Hubballi remain undelivered by the HDMC. Built in 2022, these houses are still unoccupied due to pending electrical and sanitation work. Beneficiaries, who were promised possession last September, continue to wait. The delay has led to the deterioration of the newly constructed buildings.

news.title: Police seek tenant data from apartments in Bengaluru
news.para: Kumbalgodu Police asked residents’ welfare associations asked to share details of out-of-state residents, foreign nationals and private staff
